An embedding is a vector representation of data in embedding space.

An embedding is a numerical vector that represents some piece of data (like a word, image, user, or product) inside a continuous, multi‑dimensional space called “embedding space.”

“Embedding space” is the geometric space (often 100–1000 dimensions) where similar items end up close together and dissimilar items are farther apart.


